1
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:45,950
[THE DEVIL BETWEEN US]

2
00:01:45,990 --> 00:01:48,950
[Episode 12]

3
00:01:58,550 --> 00:01:59,270
Ladies,

4
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:01,020
[2024 Nuanhai E-commerce Product
Selection Sharing Conference]

5
00:01:59,509 --> 00:02:01,240
let's start picking products.

6
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,430
Hua isn't here yet—

7
00:02:02,430 --> 00:02:03,200
should we wait for her?

8
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,070
No need.

9
00:02:04,070 --> 00:02:05,130
Let's start first.

10
00:02:05,180 --> 00:02:06,990
If we finish early, we can go eat.

11
00:02:07,150 --> 00:02:07,640
Okay.

12
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,039
Let's look at mine first.

13
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,430
This serum

14
00:02:10,449 --> 00:02:12,580
is really effective for fading spots—

15
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:15,120
the only downside is that it's expensive.

16
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:17,150
Your target customers are all young girls.

17
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:18,210
Can they afford it?

18
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:21,000
I've got a budget-friendly one here.

19
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:21,720
Take a look.

20
00:02:24,890 --> 00:02:25,980
With these ingredients,

21
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:27,360
you'll definitely get sued.

22
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:29,190
You'll lose a fortune in compensation.

23
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,520
Mine uses healthy,

24
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,750
natural herbal extracts—

25
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:32,840
absolutely safe—

26
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,400
and the price is affordable too.

27
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,840
I've been using it
for over two months now,

28
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,120
and I have sensitive skin.

29
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,810
I didn't get any allergies
even during the seasonal change this year.

30
00:02:39,810 --> 00:02:41,870
It's made with natural ingredients.

31
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:43,310
Why does your face

32
00:02:43,990 --> 00:02:46,590
look more and more yellow
the longer you use it?

33
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,640
That won't do.

34
00:02:49,910 --> 00:02:50,970
Actually, ladies,

35
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:51,870
I just got

36
00:02:52,430 --> 00:02:53,360
a new batch of products in.

37
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,020
They're selling really well.

38
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:56,710
But I was thinking—

39
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:58,890
if there's money to be made,
we should make it together.

40
00:02:58,890 --> 00:03:01,450
I'm currently a provincial-level agent,

41
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,750
and I'm honestly too busy
to handle everything.

42
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:06,410
Is anyone interested in
becoming my sub-agent?

43
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:07,190
What brand is it?

44
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:08,250
Is it that popular?

45
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:11,300
Is it the essence mask you've been selling
on your Moments?

46
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,020
Hong.

47
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,150
You've all heard of

48
00:03:13,170 --> 00:03:14,290
Hong from Hainan, right?

49
00:03:14,290 --> 00:03:16,430
The factories she works with are solid.

50
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:17,240
That batch of products she picked

51
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,490
has already sold out like crazy in Hainan.

52
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:21,840
Her sheet masks really sell that well?

53
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,079
Of course.

54
00:03:23,079 --> 00:03:24,000
What kind of margins are we talking about?

55
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:24,750
How much can we actually make?

56
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:25,430
Sorry.

57
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:26,950
Sorry, ladies.

58
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:28,520
Hua.

59
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,840
I was chatting with some business owners

60
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:31,630
from the city around noon

61
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:33,360
and totally lost track of time.

62
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,360
What are you all talking about?

63
00:03:35,550 --> 00:03:36,630
Xiaoya just said

64
00:03:36,630 --> 00:03:38,140
she wants to share
a money-making opportunity

65
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:39,000
with everyone.

66
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,440
Wow, that generous, huh?

67
00:03:42,910 --> 00:03:43,860
Of course.

68
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:45,610
I, Li Xiaoya,

69
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:47,170
have always believed that
if there's money to be made,

70
00:03:47,170 --> 00:03:48,600
we all make it together—

71
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:50,200
unlike some people

72
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,360
who are so cheap

73
00:03:51,510 --> 00:03:53,720
you can't get a dime out of them.

74
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,120
Is that so?

75
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:58,710
You actually want to
share the profits with everyone?

76
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,680
This "money-making opportunity"

77
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:05,010
wouldn't happen to be the sheet masks
you're selling right now, would it?

78
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:06,060
Yeah, it's that one.

79
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:08,570
Xiaoya said she got the stock from Hong.

80
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:10,790
So it really is this product.

81
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:13,640
I was just talking about it
with some business people earlier.

82
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,080
You guys seriously don't know?

83
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:15,940
What happened?

84
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:17,130
So Hong's scandal

85
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,209
blew up.

86
00:04:19,350 --> 00:04:22,160
All those sales numbers
she'd been bragging about

87
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,110
were fake.

88
00:04:24,290 --> 00:04:25,430
Now distributors and agents

89
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:26,870
from all over the country

90
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:29,520
have gone to Hainan
to demand their money back.

91
00:04:29,790 --> 00:04:31,550
Honestly, she's something else.

92
00:04:31,550 --> 00:04:33,190
She took the payments

93
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,159
and ran a long time ago.

94
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:37,020
That's ridiculous.

95
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:37,730
By the way,

96
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:38,840
Xiaoya,

97
00:04:39,170 --> 00:04:42,200
you must have heard about
this way earlier.

98
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,290
Why didn't you go to Hainan?

99
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:47,760
See,

100
00:04:47,830 --> 00:04:49,870
Xiaoya's the smart one.

101
00:04:50,420 --> 00:04:52,060
What's the point of going to Hainan?

102
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:53,830
You can't get their money back anyway.

103
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:55,280
Might as well stay here

104
00:04:55,310 --> 00:04:56,780
and rope a few people in

105
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,360
to help share the losses,

106
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,190
right?

107
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:01,230
Xiaoya,

108
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:02,910
that's really shady of you!

109
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,590
Don't listen to her nonsense.

110
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,680
I had no idea about

111
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:13,780
Hong's scandal.

112
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,720
Whatever's going on with her
has nothing to do with me.

113
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:18,430
The product is still selling
just fine on my end.

114
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:21,130
So are you in or not?

115
00:05:24,070 --> 00:05:25,190
If not, forget it.

116
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,000
It's totally voluntary.

117
00:05:27,670 --> 00:05:29,000
I'm not forcing anyone.

118
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:30,360
Li Xiaoya,

119
00:05:30,650 --> 00:05:32,180
I don't usually admit this,

120
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:34,080
but I gotta hand it to you—

121
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:35,630
your mouth is sharp.

122
00:05:37,310 --> 00:05:39,680
Has it really been six, seven years

123
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,230
since we met at the county radio station?

124
00:05:41,230 --> 00:05:42,840
We're old friends.

125
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:45,690
Who doesn't lose a little money
in business?

126
00:05:46,170 --> 00:05:47,850
Listen, as your older sister,

127
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,680
I gotta say—

128
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:52,260
you've got zero talent for this.

129
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,640
Just go home, take it easy,

130
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:57,340
and stop piling up debt.

131
00:06:01,690 --> 00:06:02,890
I didn't even bring up

132
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:03,830
all the messy stuff she did before

133
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:05,290
just to give her some face.

134
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:05,920
Come on.

135
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,180
Let's not talk about her.

136
00:06:07,180 --> 00:06:08,310
Let's talk about us.

137
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,460
I'm going downstairs.

138
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:09,080
What are you doing here?

139
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:13,480
I just finished dinner with some friends.

140
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,280
What's wrong?

141
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:15,380
Nothing.

142
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,530
Why are you here?

143
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:18,070
We're here to report on work.

144
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:19,730
We'll head back after eating.

145
00:07:19,830 --> 00:07:20,870
I won't keep you company today then.

146
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:21,560
I have things to do at home.

147
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,490
I'm leaving now.

148
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:23,200
Is everything really okay?

149
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,120
I'm fine.

150
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:25,510
What could be wrong?

151
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:26,720
Go ahead. Drive safe.

152
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:27,870
Take care.

153
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:28,950
Bye.

154
00:07:28,970 --> 00:07:29,530
Bye.

155
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:35,450
What a loser.

156
00:07:36,159 --> 00:07:38,360
Always pretending to be rich every day.

157
00:07:38,909 --> 00:07:41,240
Bet you're hanging onto some idiot again.

158
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:43,960
Who are you cursing at?

159
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:45,560
Who are you?

160
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,190
I'm nobody.

161
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:46,720
I just heard you cussing someone

162
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,430
and wanted to cuss you back.

163
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:48,120
What's she done to you?

164
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:48,680
Go on.

165
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,159
What did she do to you?

166
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:49,680
Try saying one more word.

167
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,580
Who are you calling a loser?

168
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:51,159
Who are you calling a loser?

169
00:07:51,159 --> 00:07:51,630
I said it.

170
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,070
What do you mean by loser?

171
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:52,430
I said it. So what?

172
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:53,870
What does it have to do with you?

173
00:07:53,870 --> 00:07:54,630
Okay, okay, lady.

174
00:07:54,630 --> 00:07:55,720
Get in the car.

175
00:07:55,870 --> 00:07:56,830
Seriously.

176
00:07:57,650 --> 00:07:58,409
Crazy.

177
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,270
Eat.

178
00:08:26,270 --> 00:08:27,660
We have work to do when we get back.

179
00:08:27,660 --> 00:08:28,310
I'm full.

180
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:29,570
Finish up and let's go.

181
00:08:34,539 --> 00:08:35,850
The Hu Wenjing I know,

182
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,870
is calm, rational,

183
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:38,850
and professional.

184
00:08:38,850 --> 00:08:40,200
What's wrong with you today?

185
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,030
Who is this person you know?

186
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:42,200
Introduce me to her.

187
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:56,510
I know what's bothering you.

188
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,400
But you shouldn't be upset now.

189
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,910
If you hadn't doubted back then,
you wouldn't be feeling this way.

190
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:02,670
And since you did doubt,

191
00:09:02,670 --> 00:09:04,530
you have no reason to be upset now.

192
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:09,030
I shouldn't have doubted her.

193
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:10,500
I've known her my whole life.

194
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,340
Now I don't

195
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,440
even know what to think.

196
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:18,110
Look.

197
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:19,840
Let's put it this way.

198
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,700
You're the boss here,

199
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:21,830
so I won't go on about

200
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,260
how everything should be doubted.

201
00:09:24,260 --> 00:09:25,190
I'm just saying:

202
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,500
if my dad's a suspect,

203
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:27,720
I'll investigate.

204
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,790
If he breaks the law,

205
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:29,320
I'll arrest him.

206
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,450
And if it's your mom,

207
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:39,010
I'll stay out of it
to avoid any conflict of interest.

208
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:47,220
[Li Xiaoya]

209
00:09:52,450 --> 00:09:53,670
[Voice Call]

210
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:03,550
Call her if you want.

211
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:05,120
Say whatever you want to say.

212
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,650
Don't beat around the bush.

213
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,320
I just wanted to check:

214
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:22,200
you rushed off just now.

215
00:10:23,180 --> 00:10:24,310
Is everything okay?

216
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:25,470
I'm fine.

217
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:28,010
It's just a small business hiccup,

218
00:10:28,310 --> 00:10:29,360
easy to fix.

219
00:10:30,490 --> 00:10:31,380
Scold me?

220
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,820
That's normal.

221
00:10:33,850 --> 00:10:34,980
She's just jealous.

222
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:36,670
I'm really fine.

223
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:38,350
Why would I be angry with her?

224
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:40,270
I'm not short of money—

225
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:41,720
if I am, I'd come to you.

226
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,510
okay?

227
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:44,680
Don't work too hard.

228
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,940
Take care of yourself.

229
00:10:47,210 --> 00:10:47,940
Don't worry.

230
00:10:48,010 --> 00:10:49,540
Let's hang out another day.

231
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:03,840
Go on.

232
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:45,960
It's pitch black.

233
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,820
Why didn't you turn on the lights?

234
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:53,990
You poor thing.

235
00:11:54,020 --> 00:11:56,150
You're eating instant noodles again?

236
00:11:58,610 --> 00:12:01,470
You're getting caught up
in research and spy stuff?

237
00:12:05,490 --> 00:12:07,750
Do you think I'll ever succeed in my life?

238
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:11,580
That depends on
what you mean by "success."

239
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:16,130
I mean making a name for myself

240
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:17,330
and making big money.

241
00:12:18,790 --> 00:12:20,120
You know, in this world,

242
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,480
there are a lot of people with big dreams

243
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,910
but fragile luck.

244
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,270
Often, it's because they lack ability.

245
00:12:28,270 --> 00:12:29,330
But that's not you.

246
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:31,400
You're just unlucky this time.

247
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:36,790
Don't bother sugarcoating it for me.

248
00:12:37,310 --> 00:12:38,190
I'm not.

249
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:40,390
I believe in you.

250
00:12:40,390 --> 00:12:42,050
You will definitely succeed.

251
00:12:53,510 --> 00:12:54,510
Round and round…

252
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:57,690
I never thought the person
who believes in me the most

253
00:12:57,690 --> 00:12:59,090
would be right beside me.

254
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:00,730
I always have been.

255
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:04,030
Why are you suddenly telling me this?

256
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:07,730
I went to see Cheng Ken.

257
00:13:08,870 --> 00:13:09,670
Li Xiaoya,

258
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,090
are you out of your mind?

259
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,120
Snap out of it!

260
00:13:13,670 --> 00:13:15,600
Dealing drugs will get you killed!

261
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:16,870
I knew you'd get tempted—

262
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:17,750
I shouldn't have told you!

263
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:18,680
I'm telling you,

264
00:13:21,430 --> 00:13:23,690
I've spent all the money Ding Lai gave us.

265
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:24,960
If we don't figure something out,

266
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,520
the rest of our lives are over.

267
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,460
What's more important, money or your life?

268
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:29,740
You're blinded by cash.

269
00:13:29,740 --> 00:13:31,830
Don't you have to pay with your life
if you kill someone?

270
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:34,630
Can you guarantee the police
will never catch you?

271
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:36,470
Do you want to spend the rest of our lives

272
00:13:36,470 --> 00:13:39,480
worrying about poverty?

273
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:47,120
I've made up my mind.

274
00:13:47,820 --> 00:13:49,460
We'll do it the way

275
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:51,840
Ding Lai planned

276
00:13:54,380 --> 00:13:55,840
and pull off one big score.

277
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:57,740
Once it's done, we're gone.

278
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:00,510
Gone?

279
00:14:00,530 --> 00:14:01,320
Where to?

280
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:02,910
Go abroad.

281
00:14:04,180 --> 00:14:05,110
The two of us.

282
00:14:13,020 --> 00:14:15,380
We can leave your mom

283
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:16,770
a lot of money—

284
00:14:17,950 --> 00:14:19,710
enough for the rest of her life.

285
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,770
Didn't you say you were ready?

286
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:36,050
Didn't you say you'd listen to me?

287
00:14:38,830 --> 00:14:40,200
Once we leave, there's no coming back.

288
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,050
I don't care.

289
00:14:42,670 --> 00:14:44,800
There's nothing here I'm attached to.

290
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:57,800
Cheng Ken is a good man.

291
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,540
But he's not smart.

292
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:04,490
Working with him is definitely risky.

293
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:06,700
I'm already trafficking drugs.

294
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:09,330
Why would I be afraid of risks?

295
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,160
But you're right.

296
00:15:17,390 --> 00:15:18,510
In this matter,

297
00:15:20,450 --> 00:15:21,380
we must have

298
00:15:22,180 --> 00:15:23,140
the initiative.

299
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:41,910
Xiaoyu, if you're scared,

300
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:43,550
just think of it as Jiajia.

301
00:15:43,830 --> 00:15:45,870
I'll be with you the whole time.

302
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:52,360
Dad.

303
00:15:52,980 --> 00:15:54,180
The oven.

304
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:05,510
From now on,

305
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:08,520
you can't eat milk tablets anymore.

306
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,960
If there's even one in the house,

307
00:16:11,590 --> 00:16:12,650
you can't touch it.

308
00:16:13,570 --> 00:16:14,240
Got it?

309
00:16:14,830 --> 00:16:16,750
I can give up the milk tablets,

310
00:16:17,030 --> 00:16:19,400
but I'll miss Xiaoyu.

311
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:24,830
I know.

312
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,260
You'll see each other again.

313
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:29,190
I promise,

314
00:16:30,420 --> 00:16:33,020
once I finish everything
I've got going on,

315
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:34,690
I'll let you meet.

316
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:36,630
When I have time,

317
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:38,390
I'll even learn a new skill

318
00:16:38,850 --> 00:16:40,660
so I can bake little fish cookies

319
00:16:41,590 --> 00:16:42,650
for you and Xiaoyu.

320
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,700
Say goodbye to Xiaoyu.

321
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,230
Bye, Xiaoyu.

322
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:13,960
Xiaoyu, let's go.

323
00:17:16,220 --> 00:17:17,079
Let's head out.

324
00:17:30,690 --> 00:17:32,020
Wait for me to come back.

325
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:46,720
Xiaoya.

326
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:48,010
Auntie.

327
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,420
Xiaoyu, get out of the car.

328
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:51,520
Auntie.

329
00:18:51,550 --> 00:18:53,280
This is the kid I told you about.

330
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,200
My friend

331
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,400
is really too busy,

332
00:18:58,030 --> 00:18:59,600
so he has no time to take care of her.

333
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:00,440
She… well,

334
00:19:01,830 --> 00:19:03,070
she does have some issues—

335
00:19:03,070 --> 00:19:03,720
she can't be left alone.

336
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:04,790
This way.

337
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:06,320
Go upstairs.

338
00:19:06,830 --> 00:19:07,590
Don't worry.

339
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,670
I'll take them in to have a look.

340
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:11,610
You should go back and rest first.

341
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:12,410
That works.

342
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:13,510
Just call me if you need anything.

343
00:19:13,510 --> 00:19:14,110
Okay.

344
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:16,630
Thank you.

345
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:18,490
Sorry to trouble you, Auntie.

346
00:19:20,970 --> 00:19:23,170
This house belonged to my grandmother.

347
00:19:23,770 --> 00:19:24,960
After she passed away,

348
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:25,950
she left it to my mom,

349
00:19:25,950 --> 00:19:27,210
and my mom gave it to me.

350
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:28,070
Auntie

351
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:29,230
lives over there.

352
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:31,780
She usually takes care of this house.

353
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:41,580
Auntie keeps this place pretty clean.

354
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:42,910
She cleans it every day.

355
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:50,840
There's a room upstairs

356
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:51,830
she can sleep in.

357
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:08,830
Does Ken

358
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,950
see this silly girl as a child

359
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,360
or a young wife?

360
00:20:13,850 --> 00:20:15,380
My brother's heart is pure.

361
00:20:19,730 --> 00:20:20,490
How is it?

362
00:20:20,690 --> 00:20:21,650
Not bad, right?

363
00:20:22,670 --> 00:20:23,470
Alright then.

364
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,270
Let's go.

365
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,170
I'll go have a word with Auntie.

366
00:20:26,190 --> 00:20:27,390
You guys get settled.

367
00:20:27,550 --> 00:20:28,350
Wait a minute.

368
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:29,380
Wait a minute.

369
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:34,750
This is

370
00:20:35,110 --> 00:20:36,820
the starting point of our partnership.

371
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:39,420
There are many things
we need to clarify today.

372
00:20:44,790 --> 00:20:45,270
Sit.

373
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:05,780
First,

374
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,970
I need to stress something:

375
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,720
what we're doing now

376
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:12,520
is a life-or-death deal.

377
00:21:15,130 --> 00:21:15,930
The three of us

378
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,740
have to stick together

379
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:22,030
and follow my plan to the letter.

380
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:24,470
Second...

381
00:21:24,470 --> 00:21:25,510
Second what?

382
00:21:25,740 --> 00:21:27,940
I don't even agree with the first point.

383
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:30,940
What do you mean
"follow your plan to the letter"?

384
00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:32,010
What plan?

385
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:33,310
Is it detailed? Thought out?

386
00:21:33,310 --> 00:21:34,440
Guaranteed to work?

387
00:21:34,550 --> 00:21:36,410
Have you ever dealt drugs before?

388
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,360
Or have you ever met a drug dealer?

389
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,230
Have you?

390
00:21:45,650 --> 00:21:46,610
Well, no.

391
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:49,570
We are all ordinary people.

392
00:21:50,410 --> 00:21:52,270
We don't understand this circle.

393
00:21:53,070 --> 00:21:55,160
And I've already proven with my actions

394
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:57,020
that we can't even get close to it.

395
00:21:58,470 --> 00:21:58,990
But

396
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:02,510
that's a mindset problem.

397
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,370
Who says drugs have to be sold to addicts?

398
00:22:05,990 --> 00:22:07,600
When you sell a product,

399
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,360
you sell it to people

400
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:10,750
who have a demand.

401
00:22:11,370 --> 00:22:13,170
What we're selling isn't drugs.

402
00:22:13,670 --> 00:22:16,680
It's a diet pill that doesn't exist
anywhere else on the market.

403
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,760
Drugs are sold to addicts.

404
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:20,710
Diet pills are sold to people
who want to lose weight.

405
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:22,090
Addicts are hard to find.

406
00:22:22,090 --> 00:22:25,150
People who want to lose weight
are everywhere you look.

407
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:29,610
Not bad.

408
00:22:30,360 --> 00:22:31,120
Very good.

409
00:22:33,230 --> 00:22:34,690
I think your idea is great.

410
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:36,830
I admit that,

411
00:22:37,170 --> 00:22:38,370
but it lacks details.

412
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,240
How exactly are we going to pull it off?

413
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,710
Do you know where these goods

414
00:22:41,710 --> 00:22:42,600
are produced?

415
00:22:42,870 --> 00:22:44,000
How to package them?

416
00:22:44,150 --> 00:22:45,150
How do we operate?

417
00:22:45,790 --> 00:22:46,880
How to market them?

418
00:22:47,230 --> 00:22:48,300
How do we get people to buy them?

419
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:49,230
How to ship them?

420
00:22:53,490 --> 00:22:55,620
That's the part you need to figure out.

421
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:56,910
I provide the supply

422
00:22:57,030 --> 00:22:58,150
and the strategic direction.

423
00:22:58,150 --> 00:23:00,130
You've only provided
the supply and direction,

424
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:00,960
but I'm

425
00:23:01,860 --> 00:23:04,970
the one who's going to execute

426
00:23:05,710 --> 00:23:07,440
and shape the whole operation,

427
00:23:08,570 --> 00:23:09,920
so you should be listening to me.

428
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:12,110
I put my life and my daughter's life

429
00:23:12,110 --> 00:23:13,310
in your hands.

430
00:23:13,690 --> 00:23:14,410
Is that ridiculous?

431
00:23:14,410 --> 00:23:16,480
Then isn't it just as ridiculous

432
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:19,460
that I'm putting the rest of my life
in your hands?

433
00:23:19,460 --> 00:23:21,390
We haven't even done anything yet,

434
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,900
and we're already turning on each other.

435
00:23:25,490 --> 00:23:26,820
If we can't stay united,

436
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:29,620
we might as well call it quits right here.

437
00:23:45,850 --> 00:23:46,480
Ken,

438
00:23:47,750 --> 00:23:49,350
finish what you were saying.

439
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:50,830
You said

440
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:52,550
"second."

441
00:23:53,430 --> 00:23:54,760
Wwhat comes after that?

442
00:24:00,810 --> 00:24:01,340
I forgot.

443
00:24:02,360 --> 00:24:03,200
See?

444
00:24:03,410 --> 00:24:05,270
All those drugs fried your brain.

445
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:06,960
Second...

446
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:08,350
Second,

447
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:09,790
regarding the profits,

448
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:10,960
I take 50%, you take 30%,

449
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:12,100
and Xiaodong, you take 20%.

450
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:12,860
Impossible.

451
00:24:13,470 --> 00:24:14,550
Are you kidding me?

452
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:16,450
I'm the one selling the goods.

453
00:24:16,450 --> 00:24:18,370
I take the highest risk.

454
00:24:18,750 --> 00:24:20,750
Why should you get the lion's share?

455
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:22,440
I want half.

456
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:24,060
You get 30%.

457
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:26,890
Without my supply, what would you sell?

458
00:24:26,890 --> 00:24:27,800
If you're so capable,

459
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,360
go sell it on the street yourself.

460
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:30,760
Can you two stop arguing?

461
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:40,350
I don't want a share anymore.

462
00:24:40,350 --> 00:24:41,810
You split it fifty-fifty.

463
00:24:42,310 --> 00:24:43,910
Xiaoya knows business best,

464
00:24:44,750 --> 00:24:45,810
so you handle that side.

465
00:24:45,810 --> 00:24:46,870
You keep the books.

466
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,220
I'll handle counter-surveillance.

467
00:24:52,530 --> 00:24:53,910
You two fill in the gaps.

468
00:24:54,990 --> 00:24:55,550
Ken,

469
00:24:56,350 --> 00:24:57,880
you handle the big picture,

470
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,020
but there's one thing.

471
00:25:00,560 --> 00:25:02,660
You've got to stop chewing that stuff.

472
00:25:02,660 --> 00:25:03,510
You must quit.

473
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:04,850
If you keep doing it,

474
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:06,070
the two of us

475
00:25:06,090 --> 00:25:06,620
are out.

476
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:10,880
Deal?

477
00:25:13,910 --> 00:25:14,600
Okay.

478
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,330
Do you agree?

479
00:25:21,070 --> 00:25:21,830
Fine.

480
00:25:22,450 --> 00:25:23,510
Then it's settled.

481
00:25:26,390 --> 00:25:27,030
Go get

482
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,520
the kid settled.

483
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:31,570
The two of us will go see her aunt.

484
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,350
We need to find a place

485
00:25:33,510 --> 00:25:34,370
to use as a base.

486
00:25:44,530 --> 00:25:46,460
I really want to make you walk back.

487
00:25:46,670 --> 00:25:47,600
What did she say?

488
00:25:48,020 --> 00:25:48,700
Xiaoyu!

489
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:50,280
Xiaoyu!

490
00:25:52,030 --> 00:25:53,090
Make you walk back.

491
00:25:53,420 --> 00:25:54,750
Xiaoyu, we're leaving.

492
00:26:13,270 --> 00:26:15,000
Why do we have to deal with this?

493
00:26:15,610 --> 00:26:16,990
I can't keep it at my house.

494
00:26:16,990 --> 00:26:17,650
It's dirty.

495
00:26:37,030 --> 00:26:40,690
All the empty houses nearby
have already been checked by the cops.

496
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:43,050
We rented this place

497
00:26:44,310 --> 00:26:46,910
because it's convenient
for what we're doing.

498
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:48,470
Hiding in plain sight

499
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,560
actually makes it safer.

500
00:27:04,070 --> 00:27:06,870
Most of my clients on social media
are young women.

501
00:27:07,270 --> 00:27:09,480
They have a huge demand for weight loss.

502
00:27:10,210 --> 00:27:11,590
Our costs are very low,

503
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,680
so we can let them try it for free.

504
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,200
We need to lower the ratio

505
00:27:58,750 --> 00:28:01,240
and stick to the method you used
for the milk tablets before—

506
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,170
make the product

507
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:03,690
into small white pills,

508
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,830
then mix them with spirulina tablets,

509
00:28:05,830 --> 00:28:06,880
vitamins,

510
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:07,880
and painkillers.

511
00:28:08,140 --> 00:28:09,550
Remove all the packaging

512
00:28:09,710 --> 00:28:11,240
and sell them as a combo set,

513
00:28:11,330 --> 00:28:15,330
so they can't tell which ingredient
is responsible for the main effect.

514
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:23,820
There are tons of

515
00:28:23,820 --> 00:28:25,750
unregulated diet pills out there.

516
00:28:26,810 --> 00:28:28,340
Whether it sells like crazy

517
00:28:28,590 --> 00:28:30,500
all comes down to the results.

518
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,020
But I can guarantee

519
00:28:32,130 --> 00:28:33,200
this batch will be

520
00:28:33,710 --> 00:28:35,360
the strongest on the market.

521
00:28:37,050 --> 00:28:38,010
Are we going to

522
00:28:39,940 --> 00:28:41,820
get some young person

523
00:28:42,070 --> 00:28:43,600
hooked on drugs doing this?

524
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:49,350
What are you playing at?

525
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,200
Are you acting all righteous now?

526
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,550
Wasn't this diet pills scheme
your idea in the first place?

527
00:28:52,550 --> 00:28:54,350
Where was your conscience then?

528
00:28:54,350 --> 00:28:55,000
Let me tell you,

529
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,600
if anyone's going to hell,
you'll be first.

530
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:57,730
Why are you yelling?

531
00:28:58,750 --> 00:29:01,010
He just had a moment of softheartedness.

532
00:29:01,790 --> 00:29:02,310
Ken,

533
00:29:02,790 --> 00:29:04,190
there's no turning back.

534
00:29:05,230 --> 00:29:07,250
Since you've started down this path,

535
00:29:07,250 --> 00:29:09,250
you have to see it through to the end.

536
00:29:09,990 --> 00:29:11,270
Thinking like that

537
00:29:11,970 --> 00:29:13,100
will get us killed.

538
00:29:24,130 --> 00:29:24,890
Got it.

539
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:26,310
I'll see it through.

540
00:29:27,550 --> 00:29:29,310
As long as my daughter lives well,

541
00:29:29,310 --> 00:29:31,570
I don't care
if the rest of the world dies.

542
00:29:32,530 --> 00:29:33,660
That's more like it.

543
00:29:34,700 --> 00:29:36,110
Since we're at the table,

544
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,550
we're going all in.

545
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:39,940
If you're not ruthless,

546
00:29:40,570 --> 00:29:41,430
how can you win?

547
00:29:53,980 --> 00:29:54,910
I just posted it,

548
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:58,620
and someone already placed an order.

549
00:29:58,930 --> 00:30:00,090
Let's hurry up.

550
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:12,720
Zhang Yan said,

551
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,440
Cao Jinchuan didn't make it to Xiamen.

552
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:16,880
He got off at a small station
called Tuzhou.

553
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:19,100
Then he stole a bike there,

554
00:30:19,130 --> 00:30:20,620
and rode it back to Nuanfeng County.

555
00:30:20,620 --> 00:30:23,020
Can you believe he pedaled
all the way back?

556
00:30:23,170 --> 00:30:24,760
He's got a lot of nerve.

557
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:26,640
Does he think the most dangerous place

558
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:27,550
is the safest?

559
00:30:27,550 --> 00:30:28,270
Who knows?

560
00:30:28,270 --> 00:30:29,510
Who knows what he's thinking?

561
00:30:29,510 --> 00:30:30,110
Isn't he just waiting

562
00:30:30,110 --> 00:30:31,440
for us to catch him?

563
00:30:32,270 --> 00:30:33,680
If we catch Cao Jinchuan,

564
00:30:34,030 --> 00:30:36,960
we can follow the trail
and track down that shipment.

565
00:30:43,790 --> 00:30:44,400
Mr. Tang,

566
00:30:44,790 --> 00:30:45,880
we need to talk to you.

567
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:46,680
What is it?

568
00:30:46,950 --> 00:30:48,220
Come outside with me.

569
00:30:49,130 --> 00:30:49,890
Follow me.

570
00:30:55,890 --> 00:30:56,280
Go.

571
00:30:56,310 --> 00:30:56,640
Go in!

572
00:31:37,180 --> 00:31:38,510
Who are you looking for?

573
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:39,200
Hello.

574
00:31:39,220 --> 00:31:40,770
Is Cao Jinchuan here?

575
00:31:41,630 --> 00:31:42,910
Chuan isn't here.

576
00:31:43,750 --> 00:31:44,830
Is something wrong?

577
00:31:44,830 --> 00:31:46,370
Grandma, let me help you out first.

578
00:31:46,370 --> 00:31:48,080
We have some questions for you.

579
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:48,480
Go in!

580
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:05,510
It's okay.

581
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:06,810
Don't be afraid.

582
00:32:07,260 --> 00:32:07,830
Grandma,

583
00:32:08,110 --> 00:32:09,350
I need to ask you something.

584
00:32:09,350 --> 00:32:11,610
How many days has Cao Jinchuan been back?

585
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,860
Chuan has been back for a few days.

586
00:32:14,380 --> 00:32:16,210
He went out early this morning.

587
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:19,320
I really don't know where he went.

588
00:32:19,430 --> 00:32:21,230
He went out this morning, right?

589
00:32:21,620 --> 00:32:22,820
What happened?

590
00:32:23,120 --> 00:32:24,420
Nothing. We're just looking for him

591
00:32:24,420 --> 00:32:25,680
to ask some questions.

592
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:26,880
And we need him

593
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:27,880
to help with something.

594
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,640
It's nothing serious. Don't be afraid.

595
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:30,350
Wenjing,

596
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:31,480
come up here.

597
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:32,970
Take care of her.

598
00:32:34,350 --> 00:32:35,750
Grandma, let me help you.

599
00:32:42,670 --> 00:32:44,600
There are about 200,000 yuan here.

600
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:45,790
So he hasn't left.

601
00:32:45,790 --> 00:32:47,590
He just went out for a bit, right?

602
00:32:47,990 --> 00:32:48,770
Put everything back the way it was.

603
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:49,450
Set up surveillance around the area.

604
00:32:49,450 --> 00:32:50,850
Wait for him to come back.

605
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:56,480
Ken.

606
00:33:08,350 --> 00:33:09,210
What are you doing here?

607
00:33:09,210 --> 00:33:09,900
Nothing.

608
00:33:09,930 --> 00:33:11,390
I just came to check on you.

609
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:13,400
Aren't you going to invite me in?

610
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:15,510
Just say it here.

611
00:33:16,450 --> 00:33:17,250
How come...

612
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:18,560
I thought you left.

613
00:33:19,950 --> 00:33:20,440
No.

614
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:22,640
I've been thinking these past few days,

615
00:33:23,980 --> 00:33:25,410
and the more I think about it,
the more it feels wrong.

616
00:33:25,410 --> 00:33:26,040
What?

617
00:33:26,450 --> 00:33:28,450
Baocai died after taking your drug.

618
00:33:29,290 --> 00:33:31,220
I ran away entirely because of you.

619
00:33:31,620 --> 00:33:32,210
Right?

620
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,520
So I came

621
00:33:34,970 --> 00:33:36,500
to ask for some travel expenses.

622
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:38,300
That's not too much to ask, is it?

623
00:33:39,420 --> 00:33:39,940
Yes,

624
00:33:40,430 --> 00:33:41,480
I know it hasn't been easy.

625
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:41,880
But,

626
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,330
we already cleared this up last time.

627
00:33:44,660 --> 00:33:46,720
You were the one who took me to Baocai.

628
00:33:48,210 --> 00:33:48,960
I'm not blaming you.

629
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:49,400
I really am not.

630
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,070
I don't blame you.

631
00:33:50,070 --> 00:33:51,170
I really don't blame you.

632
00:33:51,170 --> 00:33:51,750
It's just that...

633
00:33:51,750 --> 00:33:53,410
I really can't help right now.

634
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:54,440
But I...

635
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:55,000
I want to help you,

636
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,640
but I don't have any money.

637
00:33:56,730 --> 00:33:57,640
You sold that stuff,

638
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:59,920
and you're telling me you've got no money?

639
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:01,070
I didn't sell any—

640
00:34:01,090 --> 00:34:01,440
I swear.

641
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:01,960
I haven't sold...

642
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:03,400
I didn't sell a single bit.

643
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:04,810
I have nowhere to sell them.

644
00:34:04,810 --> 00:34:06,340
I can't turn them into cash.

645
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:07,270
Well,

646
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:08,920
that works too.

647
00:34:10,100 --> 00:34:11,449
I have a friend in Chunzhou

648
00:34:11,449 --> 00:34:13,710
who just happens to be looking for goods.

649
00:34:14,050 --> 00:34:15,909
Sounds a lot like what you've got.

650
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,840
Hand the goods over to me.

651
00:34:23,100 --> 00:34:24,350
I don't have them at home.

652
00:34:24,350 --> 00:34:26,080
I was afraid to keep them there.

653
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:28,920
I left them with a friend.

654
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:29,550
I swear.

655
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:34,280
I think you don't understand
the situation right now.

656
00:34:35,570 --> 00:34:37,489
I've got nothing to lose.

657
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,560
I'll take you down with me if I have to.

658
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:40,400
If I go to prison tomorrow,

659
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:42,400
at least I'll have a place to retire.

660
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,139
But you're different.

661
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:46,800
You have a sick daughter, right?

662
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:47,710
I asked around.

663
00:34:47,710 --> 00:34:48,400
It's fine.

664
00:34:48,489 --> 00:34:49,420
I'm begging you.

665
00:34:49,550 --> 00:34:50,630
Please.

666
00:34:51,900 --> 00:34:53,170
My daughter is sick.

667
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:55,409
It's not easy for me.

668
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:56,940
I really struggle.

669
00:34:56,940 --> 00:34:57,480
I'm on my own,

670
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:58,540
taking care of her.

671
00:34:58,590 --> 00:34:59,430
I was planning to

672
00:34:59,430 --> 00:35:01,020
sell those things

673
00:35:01,230 --> 00:35:02,710
to get money to save her.

674
00:35:03,950 --> 00:35:05,030
I need to cure her.

675
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:09,850
Save her life?

676
00:35:12,300 --> 00:35:13,700
Who's going to save mine?

677
00:35:18,830 --> 00:35:19,870
If I go down,

678
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:22,850
do you think you'll be okay?

679
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:25,520
If you stay safe,

680
00:35:28,170 --> 00:35:29,300
she'll be safe.

681
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:33,700
Right?

682
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:41,440
Yes.

683
00:35:42,630 --> 00:35:43,320
Yes.

684
00:35:43,610 --> 00:35:44,260
Let's go.

685
00:35:52,850 --> 00:35:53,890
I lied to you.

686
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:55,880
I hid the stuff...

687
00:36:00,590 --> 00:36:01,440
It's really,

688
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,130
really behind that back

689
00:36:04,670 --> 00:36:05,400
pool.

690
00:38:34,730 --> 00:38:35,330
Go inside!

691
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:36,560
Go inside!

692
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:21,430
I'm sorry.

693
00:39:23,520 --> 00:39:24,380
I'm sorry. I...

694
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:30,340
I shouldn't have let you see that.

695
00:39:31,300 --> 00:39:32,370
He was a bad man.

696
00:39:33,270 --> 00:39:34,470
He wanted to hurt you.

697
00:39:34,810 --> 00:39:35,960
I have to protect you.

698
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:37,630
I can't let anyone hurt you.

699
00:39:42,320 --> 00:39:43,190
Listen to me,

700
00:39:43,590 --> 00:39:44,320
now...

701
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:46,000
Now,

702
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,720
stay in this room.

703
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:49,380
Don't go anywhere.

704
00:39:49,510 --> 00:39:51,640
Don't come out no matter what you hear.

705
00:39:52,460 --> 00:39:54,660
I'll come back and open the door for you.

706
00:40:06,590 --> 00:40:07,280
I know.

707
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,330
Don't be scared.

708
00:40:28,370 --> 00:40:29,300
Don't be scared.

709
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:22,170
Xiaodong,

710
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:25,100
come to my house right now.

711
00:41:25,950 --> 00:41:26,610
Right now.

712
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:49,720
[Next Episode Preview]
